WinWCP - Window Whole Cell Program

The files contained in this archive can be buit using the Embarcadero Delphi software development environment which can be downloaded from https://www.embarcadero.com/products/delphi/starter

To build and run the application:
 
1) Clone this repository to a folder in the DelphiProjects folder e.g. ..\My Documents\Embarcadero\Studio\Projects\WinWCP
2) Select File > Open Project and open .. \My Documents\Embarcadero\Studio\Projects\WinEDR\WinWCP
3) Select Project > Build > All
4) Select Run

Note. The SESComponents package of common Delphi components used in Strathclyde Electrophysiology Software applications must be downloaded from https://github.com/johndempster/SESComponentsXE and installed on the Delphi toolbar before building this application. See the SESComponentsXE repository  for details.

